The paper discusses automatic anomaly detection in cloud infrastructure data, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also employs statistical learning techniques, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with social network data, which could fall under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses capacity planning and user behavior, which are related to Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with security and reliability, which could fall under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
